<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="58" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[113,765,602,968]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Haec species a congeneris foliorum petiolis rhachidibus petiolulisque trichomatum aureorum perbrevium stellatofasciculatorum caespitibus dense indutis atque foliolorum lamina adaxialiter dense punctata apice breviter mucronata distinguitur.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="58" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[113,764,1008,1928]" lastBlockId="13.[801,1452,282,402]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis box="[151,197,1008,1031]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Tree</emphasis>
c. 7 m tall; stems densely light brown tomentulose, glabrescent. 
<emphasis box="[245,320,1040,1064]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Petioles</emphasis>
3.5-7.5 cm, densely covered with tufts of very short, golden stellate-fasciculate trichomes. 
<emphasis box="[638,708,1072,1095]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Leaves</emphasis>
with 4-14 alternate to sub-opposite leaflets; rachis 0.8-16.6 cm, keeled above, densely covered with tufts of very short golden stellate-fasciculate trichomes; petiolule 3-5 mm, densely covered with tufts of very short golden stellate-fasciculate trichomes; leaflet blade 3.7-10.6 × 1.3-2.3 cm, narrowly elliptic, subcoriaceous, flat in pressed material, glabrous and glossy and densely punctate above, glabrous below, base markedly asymmetrical, attenuate to cuneate to rarely acute, margins slightly revolute, apex acute to acuminate, the acumen rounded and often with a short mucro, midvein raised above and below, sparsely covered with tufts of very short golden stellatefasciculate trichomes on both sides, secondary veins 13-17 per side, flat to slightly raised above and below, tertiary venation flat on both surfaces. 
<emphasis box="[335,456,1520,1544]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Inflorescence</emphasis>
axis 4.3-17 cm long, c. 1 mm in diam., unbranched, moderately covered with tufts of very short golden stellate-fasciculate trichomes; bracts c. 0.5 mm, triangular, flat, caducous; pedicels usually paired on a common peduncle to 0.5 mm, sometimes solitary and epedunculate, 2-4 mm, moderately to densely covered with tufts of very short golden stellate-fasciculate trichomes. 
<emphasis box="[577,708,1712,1736]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Male flowers</emphasis>
with a cupulate, 5-lobed calyx, the lobes broadly triangular, 0.3-0.6 × 0.2-0.5 mm, moderately covered with tufts of very short golden stellate-fasciculate trichomes outside; disc obscured by the pistillode; stamens 7-9, filaments c. 2.8 mm, with sparse spreading trichomes along basal half, anthers 1.0-1.1 × 0.6- 0.8 mm, oblong; pistillode 0.2-0.3 mm high, 0.2-0.3 mm in diam., hemispherical to depressed hemispherical, disc 0.3- 0.5 mm high, 1 mm in diam., densely covered with stiff erect golden trichomes to 0.4 mm long. 
<emphasis box="[1189,1345,346,370]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Female flowers</emphasis>
not seen. 
<emphasis box="[801,856,379,402]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fruit</emphasis>
not seen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="58" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="13.[801,1452,442,722]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis box="[839,1032,443,466]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Conservation status</emphasis>
. – While 
<taxonomicName box="[1135,1307,442,466]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Beguea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galotensis">
<emphasis box="[1135,1307,442,466]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Beguea galokensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs within the recently decreed Galoko-Kalobinono protected area (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig. 3" captionStartId="5.[113,140,1315,1334]" captionTargetBox="[113,763,276,1300]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[113,763,276,1300]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. – Geographic distribution of Begueo onkeronensis G. E. Schatz &amp; Lowry (square), B. oustrolis G. E. Schatz, Gereau &amp; Lowry (diamond), B. betomponensis G. E. Schatz, Gereau &amp; Lowry (triangle), B. golokensis G. E. Schatz &amp; Lowry (star) and B. vulgoris G. E. Schatz, Gereau &amp; Lowry (circles), mapped on the bioclimatic zones of Madagascar (after CORNET, 1974; see SCHATZ, 2000)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/888181/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
), it was collected adjacent to a clearing used as pasture and subject to potential burning, threats that may continue despite the new protected status. Therefore, with a restricted AOO and plausible threats that could rapidly push the species to Critically Endangered or Extinct status, 
<taxonomicName box="[1228,1354,634,658]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Beguea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galotensis">
<emphasis box="[1228,1354,634,658]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">B. galokensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
warrants a preliminary assessment of “Vulnerable” [VU D2] using the IUCN Red List Criteria (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" box="[1078,1220,698,722]" firstAuthor="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland &amp; Cambridge" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" refId="ref13043" refString="IUCN (2012). IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. 2 nd ed. IUCN Species Survival Commission, Gland &amp; Cambridge." title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. 2 nd ed." type="book" year="2012">IUCN, 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="58" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[801,1452,762,1266]" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">
<emphasis box="[839,897,763,786]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Notes</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName box="[933,1120,762,786]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Beguea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="galotensis">
<emphasis box="[933,1120,762,786]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Beguea galokensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from the type specimen from the Forêt de Galoko, a site of high local endemism from which a number of new species have been recently described, including 
<taxonomicName authority="Daly, Raharim. &amp; Federman" authorityName="Daly, Raharim. &amp; Federman" class="Gastropoda" family="Strombidae" genus="Canarium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Littorinimorpha" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="galotense">
<emphasis box="[1033,1246,858,882]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Canarium galokense</emphasis>
Daly, Raharim. &amp; Federman
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="DALY, D. C. &amp; J. RAHARIMAMPIONONA &amp; S. FEDERMAN" box="[926,1115,890,915]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="DALY" journalOrPublisher="Adansonia ser. 3" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" pagination="277 - 345" part="37" refId="ref13002" refString="DALY, D. C., J. RAHARIMAMPIONONA &amp; S. FEDERMAN (2015). A revision of Canarium L. (Burseraceae) in Madagascar. Adansonia ser. 3, 37: 277 - 345." title="A revision of Canarium L. (Burseraceae) in Madagascar" type="journal article" year="2015">DALY et al., 2015</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="Randrian. &amp; Lowry" authorityName="Randrian. &amp; Lowry" authorityYear="2009" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Micronychia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="benono">
<emphasis box="[1134,1338,890,914]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Micronychia benono</emphasis>
Randrian. &amp; Lowry
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="RANDRIANASOLO, A. &amp; P. P. LOWRY II" box="[922,1298,922,947]" firstAuthor="RANDRIANASOLO" journalOrPublisher="Adansonia" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" pagination="157 - 168" part="31" refId="ref13109" refString="RANDRIANASOLO, A. &amp; P. P. LOWRY II (2009). Four new species and one new combination in the Malagasy endemic genus of Micronychia Oliv. (Anacardiaceae). Adansonia ser. 3, 31: 157 - 168." title="Four new species and one new combination in the Malagasy endemic genus of Micronychia Oliv. (Anacardiaceae)" type="journal article" year="2009">RANDRIANASOLO &amp; LOWRY, 2009</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lowry &amp; Callm." authorityName="Lowry &amp; Callm." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Araliaceae" genus="Polyscias" kingdom="Plantae" order="Apiales" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aeohlhauseri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Polyscias wohlhauseri</emphasis>
Lowry &amp; Callm.
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="CALLMANDER, M. W. &amp; C. RAKOTOVAO &amp; J. RAZAFITSALAMA &amp; P. B. PHILLIPSON &amp; S. BUERKI &amp; C. HONG-WA &amp; N. RAKOTOARIVELO &amp; S. ANDRIAMBOLOLONERA &amp; M. M. KOOPMAN &amp; D. M. JOHNSON &amp; T. DEROIN &amp; A. RAVOAHANGY &amp; S. SOLO &amp; J. - N. LABAT &amp; P. P. LOWRY II" box="[1148,1444,954,978]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="CALLMANDER" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" pagination="179 - 202" part="64" refId="ref12840" refString="CALLMANDER, M. W., C. RAKOTOVAO, J. RAZAFITSALAMA, P. B. PHILLIPSON, S. BUERKI, C. HONG-WA, N. RAKOTOARIVELO, S. ANDRIAMBOLOLONERA, M. M. KOOPMAN, D. M. JOHNSON, T. DEROIN, A. RAVOAHANGY, S. SOLO, J. - N. LABAT &amp; P. P. LOWRY II (2009). New species from the Galoka and Kalebonono massifs: two unknown and severely threatened mountainous areas in NW Madagascar. Candollea 64: 179 - 202." title="New species from the Galoka and Kalebonono massifs: two unknown and severely threatened mountainous areas in NW Madagascar" type="journal article" year="2009">CALLMANDER et al., 2009</bibRefCitation>
) (
<figureCitation box="[809,873,986,1010]" captionStart="Fig. 3" captionStartId="5.[113,140,1315,1334]" captionTargetBox="[113,763,276,1300]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[113,763,276,1300]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Fig. 3. – Geographic distribution of Begueo onkeronensis G. E. Schatz &amp; Lowry (square), B. oustrolis G. E. Schatz, Gereau &amp; Lowry (diamond), B. betomponensis G. E. Schatz, Gereau &amp; Lowry (triangle), B. golokensis G. E. Schatz &amp; Lowry (star) and B. vulgoris G. E. Schatz, Gereau &amp; Lowry (circles), mapped on the bioclimatic zones of Madagascar (after CORNET, 1974; see SCHATZ, 2000)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/888181/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). It can be easily distinguished from 
<taxonomicName box="[1273,1447,986,1010]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Beguea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="13" pageNumber="58" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="betamponensis">
<emphasis box="[1273,1447,986,1010]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">B. betamponensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with which it shares an indument of tufts of very short golden stellate-fasciculate trichomes, by its subcoriaceous leaflets with slightly revolute margins, acute to acuminate apex with a distinct mucro, and flat to slightly raised secondary veins (vs very coriaceous leaflets with strongly revolute margins, rounded apex lacking a mucro, and impressed secondary veins) and its unbranched inflorescence (vs occasionally branched inflorescence) (
<figureCitation box="[962,1027,1242,1266]" captionStart="Fig. 9" captionStartId="14.[136,163,1890,1909]" captionTargetBox="[233,1384,273,1866]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[233,1384,273,1866]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Fig. 9. – Begueo golokensis G. E. Schatz &amp; Lowry. A. Flowering branch; B. Leaflet (lower surface); C. Leaflet (upper surface); D. Portion of inflorescence axis with two flowers. [Monjoto et ol. 454, P] [Drawing: R. L. Andriamiarisoa]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/888193/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="58">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
